  (145, 44, 9, 'MC-ENV-020', 'All International Bird Rescue response team members are Hazwoper certified and trained and experienced in emergency management, and the team coordinates and trains local wildlife rehabilitators and volunteers used in the wildlife response.', 'All Bird Rescue response team members are Hazwoper certified and trained, and experienced in emergency management. Team members are mobilized as needed to oversee different aspects of the wildlife response effort.', 'https://www.birdrescue.org/our-work/oil-spill-response-and-preparedness/services-offered/'),
  (146, 44, 9, 'MC-ENV-020', 'International Bird Rescue has responded to over 2,250 spills on every continent except Antarctica in its 50+ years of working in this field, providing oiled wildlife collection, rehabilitation, and documentation services.', 'Bird Rescue has responded to over 2250 spills on every continent except Antarctica in our 50+ years of working in this field.', 'https://www.birdrescue.org/our-work/oil-spill-response-and-preparedness/'),
  (147, 45, 9, 'MC-ENV-001', 'CEDRE''s laboratory can be mobilised in an emergency to determine the physical and chemical characteristics of the pollutant and its weathering over time, and can perform chemical fingerprinting in the case of an oil spill to compare samples.', 'CEDRE''s laboratory can be mobilised in an emergency to determine the physical and chemical characteristics of the pollutant and its weathering over time. We can also perform chemical fingerprinting in the case of an oil spill to compare samples.', 'https://cedre.fr/en/expertise/intervention'),
  (148, 45, 9, 'MC-ENV-001', 'CEDRE provides remote technical support including risk assessment for people and the environment and modelling of pollutant trajectory and behaviour including dispersion, evaporation, and dissolution, and has been working throughout France and worldwide as technical advisers for nearly 50 years.', 'For nearly 50 years, we have been working throughout France and worldwide as technical advisers to help you deal with spills in marine or inland waters, from small-scale incidents through to major disasters.', 'https://cedre.fr/en/expertise/intervention'),
